cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper primarily focuses on using computer vision techniques to estimate food calories, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with analyzing food images and estimating their calorie content, which can be considered as a multimedia application. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses deep learning techniques to improve the accuracy of food calorie estimation, which falls under the scope of this sub-category. 
4. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper deals with dietary assessment, which involves interaction between humans and computers. 
5. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - The paper involves retrieving information about food items from images and estimating their calorie content, which can be considered as an information retrieval task.
